# üöÄ feature request

### Description

Could you please add a `[prop.propertyA]="boundVariable"` style data binding for `@Input() propertyA = initialValue;` in a component. When the value `boundVariable` is `undefined`, the `propertyA` will be set to the `initialValue`.

```html
<my-component [prop.propertyA]="boundVariable"></my-component>
```

As in `[attr.id] = "uniqId"` for simple HTML elements, if the value of `uniqId` is `underfined`, no id will be set for the element.

```html
<div [attr.id]="uniqId">
  blahblahlbah
</id>
```

-- thanks for @abraham 's comment. added to clarify:
While you bind id like this [id]="uniqId", if the value of uniquId is undefined, the id will be assigned a string "undefined".

### Describe alternatives you've considered

To implement it in a component, the property should be impleme nted as setter/getter pair:

```typescript
  private _propertyA = initialValue; // initialValue is a const declared somewhere
  @Input() set propertyA(value) {
    if (value === undefined) {
      this._propertyA = initialValue;
    } else {
      this._propertyA = value;
    }
  }

  get propertyA() {
    return this._propertyA;
  }
```

-- thanks for @abraham 's and @petebacondarwin 's comments. added to clarify:
If you don't have control over the component you may conditionally bind the property like this without having to dive in to know the default-value of the property:

```
<component *ngIf="boundVariable !== undefined" [propertyA]="boundVariable"></component>
<component *ngIf="boundVariable === undefined"></component>
```

If the new feature is provided, a `[prop.propertyA]="boundVariable"` style data binding will save the works.

